[00:11.78]Make Me a Faithful Tree
[00:16.69]You planted me in mercy’s soil,
[00:20.39]Beside the living stream;
[00:22.56]Your hidden roots sustain my soul
[00:25.61]With grace I cannot see.
[00:28.10]O make me, Lord, a faithful tree,
[00:43.63]Well rooted firm in Thee;
[00:54.90]That all the fruit my life shall bear
[01:10.79]Brings glory unto Thee.
[01:19.07]What grows upon my waiting limbs
[01:21.44]Reveals what feeds my heart;
[01:23.79]For bitter roots bear bitter fruit,
[01:26.62]And pride will tear apart.
[01:28.74]O make me, Lord, a faithful tree,
[01:32.40]Well rooted firm in Thee;
[01:35.04]That all the fruit my life shall bear
[01:39.05]Brings glory unto Thee.
[01:41.08]A good tree cannot evil yield,
[01:43.47]Nor rotten fruit be sound;
[01:45.91]The life within determines what
[01:47.99]Upon its bough is found.
[01:50.05]Search me, Lord, and try my ways,
[01:54.29]Expose what lies beneath;
[01:56.65]Replace the stone within my chest
[01:59.81]With roots of living faith.
[02:02.56]Let living water flood my soul,
[02:06.69]Let every dry place bloom;
[02:10.55]Till branches heavy with Your grace
[02:14.43]Break forth in holy fruit.
[02:17.57]Final Refrain
[02:19.81]O keep me, Lord, a faithful tree,
[02:27.93]Well rooted firm in Thee;
[02:33.93]Till every fruit from every branch
[02:40.72]Brings praise eternally.
[02:43.81]I’m rooted in You,
[02:47.07]Rooted in You.
[02:48.81]Every branch, every leaf,
[02:51.55]All for You.
[02:53.84]Prune me, shape me,
[02:56.75]Grow Your truth.
[02:58.87]I’m rooted in You,
[03:04.16]Only You.